<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1122,1736]" pageId="2" pageNumber="530">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1642,1667]" pageId="2" pageNumber="530">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[323,455,1643,1667]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Nicolaus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abuensis">
<emphasis box="[323,455,1643,1667]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="530">N. abuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Stiller" authorityName="Stiller" box="[585,762,1642,1667]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Nicolaus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis box="[585,686,1643,1666]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="530">N. minor</emphasis>
Stiller
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[834,979,1642,1667]" name="South Africa" pageId="2" pageNumber="530">South Africa</collectingCountry>
in the general structure of the aedeagus but differs in having denticles on the mesal lobe of the pygofer process (absent in 
<taxonomicName box="[1059,1158,1678,1701]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Nicolaus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis box="[1059,1158,1678,1701]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="530">N. minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the ventral process of aedeagal shaft more strongly curved apically.
</paragraph>
